text: The Free City of Cracow was a city state created by the Congress of Vienna in 1815, which included the Polish city of Cracow and its surrounding land. It was controlled by each its three neighbors (Russia, Prussia, and Austria). In 1846, in the aftermath of the failed , the Free City of Cracow was taken over by the Austrian Empire. It was a leftover of the Duchy of Warsaw, which was partitioned among the three states after the Congress in 1815. ==Notes== == References == == Sources == * * * == Further information == * * Category:City- states Category:Former countries Category:1815 establishments in Europe
